    "content": "EVENT REPORT: AWS Cloud Mastery Series #1 ‚Äî AI/ML/GenAI on AWS Date: Saturday, November 15, 2025\nTime: 8:00 AM ‚Äì 11:30 AM\nLocation: AWS Vietnam Office, Bitexco Financial Tower, District 1, Ho Chi Minh City\nObjective: Provide foundational to advanced understanding of AI/ML services and Generative AI (GenAI) on AWS.\n1. Opening \u0026 Context (8:00 ‚Äì 8:30 AM) Registration and networking to kick off the event. Session introduced learning objectives and workshop structure. Overview of AI/ML landscape in Vietnam ‚Äî trends, opportunities, and challenges. 2. AWS AI/ML Platform Overview (8:30 ‚Äì 10:00 AM) The morning session focused on Amazon SageMaker, AWS‚Äôs fully managed end-to-end machine learning platform.\nKey Topics ML Lifecycle:\nData preparation, labeling, training, fine-tuning, deployment, and inference workflows.\nBuilt-in MLOps:\nNative MLOps capabilities in SageMaker enable automated pipeline management for production-grade ML.\nLive Demo ‚Äî SageMaker Studio:\nDemonstration of the IDE environment used for notebook development, training jobs, and model experimentation.\n10:00 ‚Äì 10:15 AM | Coffee Break 3. Generative AI with Amazon Bedrock (10:20 ‚Äì 11:30 AM) The second half of the session shifted to GenAI architecture using Amazon Bedrock and Foundation Models (FMs).\nCore Learning Points Foundation Models:\nComparison of leading models ‚Äî Claude, Llama, Titan ‚Äî and use-case model selection strategies.\nPrompt Engineering:\nPractical techniques including Chain-of-Thought reasoning and Few-shot prompting to improve model output quality.\nRetrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG):\nArchitecture, Knowledge Base integration, and how RAG boosts model accuracy using internal data.\nBedrock Agents \u0026 Guardrails:\nBuilding multi-step agent workflows and enforcing safe AI behavior using Guardrails.\nLive Demo:\nHands-on demonstration of building a simple GenAI chatbot using Bedrock components.\n11:30 AM ‚Äî Closing \u0026 Lunch Participants concluded the session and proceeded to lunch (individual arrangement).\nGENERAL EVALUATION \u0026 NEXT STEPS Evaluation The session offered strong coverage of both pillars of AI on AWS:\nSageMaker for full-cycle ML development and custom model training. Bedrock for rapid GenAI deployment using Foundation Models. Live demos provided real clarity on how organizations can adopt these services effectively.\nKey Takeaways Understanding the end-to-end ML lifecycle in SageMaker. Foundation Models, RAG, and Agents as core components of modern GenAI workloads. Recommended Next Steps Hands-on with Bedrock:\nBegin experimenting with prompt engineering using FMs like Claude or Titan to build prototypes.\nDeep-dive into SageMaker:\nExplore MLOps automation for deployment pipelines, model monitoring, and CI/CD for machine learning.\nEvent Photos",
    "description": "EVENT REPORT: AWS Cloud Mastery Series #1 ‚Äî AI/ML/GenAI on AWS Date: Saturday, November 15, 2025\nTime: 8:00 AM ‚Äì 11:30 AM\nLocation: AWS Vietnam Office, Bitexco Financial Tower, District 1, Ho Chi Minh City\nObjective: Provide foundational to advanced understanding of AI/ML services and Generative AI (GenAI) on AWS.\n1. Opening \u0026 Context (8:00 ‚Äì 8:30 AM) Registration and networking to kick off the event. Session introduced learning objectives and workshop structure. Overview of AI/ML landscape in Vietnam ‚Äî trends, opportunities, and challenges. 2. AWS AI/ML Platform Overview (8:30 ‚Äì 10:00 AM) The morning session focused on Amazon SageMaker, AWS‚Äôs fully managed end-to-end machine learning platform.",
